      "writtenOn": "2015-08-31T21:15:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the right question is why is almost everything else \u003e\u003d? I think we\u0027ve discussed by \u003e\u003d is basically a time-bomb that is just waiting to go off at any random time and we\u0027ve been bitten by it occasionally. Personally, I think we should pin everything down with \u003d\u003d. \n\nThen when we want to move, explicitly bump the version and re-test right away.\n\nSo, pbr 1.6.0 is the latest version and it works.\n\nCraig, are you suggesting that we pin this to something earlier that 1.6.0, or use \u003e\u003d 1.6.0?",
